----------------- ABOUT ----------------- ▒ ▒ img2Block is a tool that lets you convert ▒ ░ a black & white & grey image to an ascii ░ ░ block-element text file. This application ░ ▒ is meant to be a simple way to get a base ▒ ▒ line ascii file to work with. It is ▒ ▓ recommended to use a program like Pablo ▓ ▓ Draw to polish the output of this tool. ▓ █ ----------------------------------------- █ █ ----------------- USAGE ----------------- █ ▓ 1. Create an image in your paint program ▓ ▓ of choice. Colors are indexed by the ▓ ▒ order in which they appear from left ▒ ▒ to right starting in the upper corner ▒ ░ of your image. ░ ░ ░ ░ Be sure your image meets the size ░ ░ constraints! ░ ▒ Height: >1 ▒ ▒ Width: 80 ▒ ▓ ▓ ▓ Colors: use a max of three colors ▓ █ █ █ 2. After creating your image, run this █ ▓ application. Then load your image ▓ ▓ by pressing the "load" button. ▓ ▒ ▒ ▒ An image preview will be given on ▒ ░ the left. The panel on the far left ░ ░ of the window shows what character ░ ░ each color index will be converted ░ ░ to. To change the character you can ░ ▒ click the pixel image and choose a ▒ ▒ new character from the pop-up; or, ▒ ▓ you can enter a character in the ▓ ▓ text field manually. ▓ █ █ █ If you need to re-index the colors █ ▓ of your image, click the "Map Image ▓ ▓ Colors" button. You can swap colors ▓ ▒ here. If for example, you have a ▒ ▒ black background but the grey and ▒ ░ white colors need to be swapped ░ ░ in your image output, then you can ░ ░ set 0=>0; 1=>2; 2=>1; ░ ░ ░ ▒ NOTE: After re-indexing the relative ▒ ▒ order of 1,2,3 will remain. ▒ ▓ ▓ ▓ 3. Once you have your image loaded and ▓ █ settings set click on the "convert" █ █ button to generate the text. By █ ▓ default the middle index -- grey -- ▓ ▓ inserts a whole block for split ▓ ▒ pixels. A split pixel is when two ▒ ▒ pixels that are aligned vertically ▒ ░ but differ in color like such: ░ ░ ░ ░ ░ ░ ░░░░ <--pixel 1 ░ ▒ ░░░░ ▒ ▒ ████ <--pixel 2 ▒ ▓ ████ ▓ ▓ ▓ █ Since ASCII block-element characters █ █ take up only one space and must █ ▓ represent 2 pixels, this creates a ▓ ▓ problem for the faded block element ▓ ▒ characters since there is no way to ▒ ▒ represent them properly without ▒ ░ x2 scale. ░ ░ ░ ░ You may need to adjust your image ░ ░ or character selection to address ░ ▒ this issue! ▒ ▒ ▒ ▓ ▓ ▓ 4. Once this image is converted you ▓ █ can copy it directly from the █ █ text editor; or, you can save the █ ▓ image to a .txt by clicking on the ▓ ▓ save button. ▓ ▒ ▒ ▒ ----------------------------------------- ▒ ░ ░ ░ ░ ▓▄▄▄▄▄▄ ▄▄▄▄▄▄ ▄▄▄▄▄▄▄▄▄▄▄ ▄ ▄▄▄▄▄▄▄ ▄▄▄▄▄▄▄▓ █░▒██░███▄▀░██▓ ░▓█░█████████░█▓ ▀█░█████░▀ ░██ ▀ ▀▀ ▀ ▀▀ ▀▀▀▀ ▀ ▀▀▀ ▀▀ ▀▀▀▀▀▀ ▀▀▀▀ ▀ ▀▀
